d any weakness in your legs? No weakness. Okay And have you tried anything that improves the pain at all or anything that makes it worse I have tried taking some like Tylenol and Advil or NSAIDs and it has helped with the pain. I've tried icing it too, like after practice and stuff like that, which does seem to help a little bit. but yeah that's about it okay okay and other than that did you like have a fall or did you have any injuries recently before you started having this pain no it's kind of come on on its own no falls or like trauma to the knee okay and other than that are you healthy do you have any medical conditions at all all right yeah I don't have anything so healthy okay any medications that you take on a regular basis? No, nothing. I don't take anything. Okay. Any allergies? No allergies. Okay. And have you been sick recently at all with fevers, chills, any cold or viral symptoms? No, I haven't had anything like that. I've been feeling well. Okay. Any changes in your skin, like any rashes? No, I haven't had any rashes. Okay. And any kind of shortness of breath, chest pain? Nope, nothing like that. Okay. And any changes in your bowel movements or urinary patterns? No, I haven't had any changes there. Okay. And do you have any recent or past history of any hospitalizations or surgeries? No, I haven't had anything like that. Okay. And any family history of any musculoskeletal conditions or anything that runs in the family? um no nothing like that no okay okay um and uh currently right now uh um do you go to school uh do you work at all yeah i i go to school um and uh i play on the uh soccer team and uh the basketball team it's basketball season right now and in grade 10. Okay in grade 10 okay and is school going well any issues at all with bullying or anything like that No school been been going well I have been doing well in my courses and I have a good group of friends so I enjoy it It fun Okay. And what's your home situation like? Who do you live with? so I live with both of my parents and I have a younger sister as well she's in grade grade seven and we have a dog as well okay and do you generally feel safe at home as well as outside of your home environment I do yeah my I get along well with my parents and we yeah, my parents are great. That's good. And this is just wanted to let you know that anything that you talk about in here with us stays confidential and won't leave this room unless there is potential harm to yourself or others. So have you tried any recreational drugs like marijuana? Have you tried smoking or alcohol at all no i've been trying i've stayed away from that that sort of thing i've i know of other people in my class who have and stuff but i always just i'm just trying to stay uh um as ready as i can for the sports okay that's good um and uh yeah so and are you up to date with all your immunizations? Yeah, I am. Yeah, my mom made sure that I got all of that stuff done. Okay. All right. So yeah, those are some questions I had. I just have a few more questions with regards to just examining your knee. Are you able to walk or do you have any kind of a limp? No limp. I can walk okay. Okay. And are you able to run? Yeah, I can run. But when I do, it causes some pain. I'm able to still run. But yeah, it hurts. Okay. And so when you palpate your lower knee just under the patelle, you said it's a sharp pain, right? yeah exactly and then what if it's and it feels kind of achy or what when uh like after practice or something like that but if you press on it it's sharp I see um and uh any any kind of uh like are you able to flex and extend your knee uh right now if you tried I can yeah okay um and have you uh noticed any kind of um rotation of your knee at all no nothing like that no okay um okay and no weakness below your knee right no weakness I just feel like my muscles are really tight like my thigh and my hamstring muscles I I need to stretch them out some more They do just feel tight Okay and do you notice any kind of swelling or redness or bruising in the area no no okay and your ankle and hips uh you don have any pain or issues with movement right no not at all no no uh problems with my ankle or hip okay all right um yeah so those are just all the questions i had for you today do you have any questions I was just wondering what I can do to make this go away yeah so definitely this is something that is what we call jumper's knee it's fairly common amongst younger athletes especially those that play sports like volleyball or basketball but right now we don't really need to do any kind of imaging or anything like that it seems like you're in the earlier phases and it's good that you came in we definitely do need to manage it with some conservative management where we're gonna keep having taking a look at it as well as I would recommend icing it every, like for a half an hour, like around four to six times a day, especially after you're doing your activities. Then you can continue taking the Tylenol and Advil as long as you're following the maximum amount per day, depending on if you're taking extra strength, Tylenol, for example, versus the regular strength. and then I will also refer you to some physiotherapy that will kind of teach you some strengthening and stretching exercises that you can do to help what we call like what you might be having is just some inflammation in your patellar tendon right below your patella so we need to strengthen the muscles around it. So we'll do some referral to physiotherapy and then we'll see how you do based on all those treatment options. And then if it gets worse or if it doesn't get better, we might need to do some imaging, either ultrasound or an MRI, and then see where to go from there. But for now, does that sound okay with you? It does. Yeah. Thank you. So you said that you think it's like a patellar tendonitis or something like that? Yeah, it's patellar tendonitis. It's commonly called the jumper's knee. And it should resolve with the steps that we, especially since it seems like you're in the earlier stages. So it seems like it should be pretty responsive. But if it isn't, there are other steps we can discuss in the future. Okay, that sounds great. Thank you.",0.14903565166569258,0.14604810996563575,0.19598542627494775,35,130,90,1491
