␀","you tell me what brought you in today? Sure. So my son, he's two and a half months old, and we're in the ER because he's had this cough, fever, it seems like he's breathing too fast. It's been happening for the past two days, and we weren't sure what else to do for him. Okay. So the first thing here would be vital signs and assessing stability. So is there that information? We're going to say vital stable. He is on two liters of oxygen right now. Okay. So when did the symptoms specifically start? Two days ago. Okay. And what started first? um so i guess he was coughing first and then we took his temperature and it seemed like he had a fever it was over 38 um and then over the past couple of hours it just seems like he's having a hard time breathing he's breathing too fast okay so um with this cough has there has it been it. Any sputum come up? Yes. Yeah. Yellow sputum. Yellow. Okay. Any blood that you've noticed in the sputum? No. Okay. And how was the fever checked? We did a rectal. Okay. And has the temperature on uh like has it has there been a fever the entire time we checked twice we checked uh on the first day and then again last night okay um and in regards to the difficulties breathing uh has there been any like changes to um like has there been any noisy breathing I would say he sounds slightly wheezy. Okay. Have you been hearing any whistling sounds when he's breathing in? I wouldn't say whistling, no. Okay. And has he been experiencing any other symptoms No he actually he hasn gone through as many wet diapers as he normally does Okay. Has he been, well, how's his appetite been? Not the greatest, no. Okay, so not eating as much or drinking as much? Yeah. Okay, how has his behavior been? Oh, he's been very, very fussy. Okay, inconsolable, would you say? Yes, yeah. Okay, and any bowel problems? no not that we noticed okay um and any vomiting no okay um and uh have you guys been around any anybody who's been sick no okay so everybody else has been been well uh any travel uh recently um we haven't traveled recently um my mom so his grandma had traveled recently um and he saw her last week okay um where did she go um mexico okay and uh how's grandma doing now she's doing fine yeah okay um and uh and he saw he spent some time with her he spent a day with her okay i see um and uh so in regards to um past health um has he had any symptoms or like this before uh i guess last month he kind of had similar symptoms and uh they said it was a viral um infection so he was just given some puffers to help us breathing and he got better on his own okay did they tell you uh what the diagnosis was um at that time or just say that it was a viral infection No they said it could be bronchiolitis or just an upper viral infection Okay Yeah Any reasons for hospitalizations That time that he had the bronchiolitis or viral infection, he was hospitalized for two days just to help his breathing. Okay. And any medications that he takes regularly or uses regularly? Uh, he, no, no. Okay. Any, uh, allergies to medications that you're aware of? No. Okay. And, um, in regards to, um, birthing or prenatal history, were there any complications throughout pregnancy? No, I wouldn't say so. No, it was normal. Everything was normal and he was a healthy baby. Okay. Um, and, uh, has mom had any, uh, complications with any prior pregnancies? No, he's, uh, he's the first one. He's the first one. Okay. Um, and, uh, was mom well throughout the pregnancy, like no infectious symptoms, uh, during? No, no. Okay. Um, and any concerns with his growth or development so far? No, he's been normal. Okay. And then any concerns with either his vision or hearing? No. Okay. So if you... Okay. And are his immunizations up to date? Yes, they are. Okay. And could you tell me a little bit about the living situation? Who's in the home currently and where you guys are living? Yeah, so we live in a house. It's him, myself, and my husband, his dad. Okay. Any pets at home? No pets, no. Just, well, actually, goldfish. Oh, cool. And are there any concerns for, like, verbal abuse in the home? No. How about any physical abuse in the home No Okay And does anybody smoke cigarettes in the home No Okay And then how about drink alcohol We have like a glass of wine once a week. Okay. And who's the primary caregiver for him? I guess we both are. Yeah, we both are. Okay. And in the family, are there any lung conditions like asthma or any heart conditions that run in the family? My sister, so his aunt, has asthma. Okay. Okay. And does anybody, is there any congenital diseases that run in the family? No, no. Okay. How about any genetic diseases? No. okay um and um so um it's sounding like um we wanted to do a uh a workup for um his symptoms right now for breathing heavily and uh with the the fever that's concerning for uh a type of infection and with being under three months, it would warrant some investigations. So we'd want to check, do some blood tests and check his cerebrospinal fluid as well to make sure that there's no infection in the brain, I guess. And we'll kind of go from there. Sure. Yeah, that sounds good. Okay. In the meantime, yeah, we'll give you some inhalers and keep the oxygen on to help with the lungs and the breathing. And then keep monitoring for how he's doing symptomatically. Okay. Thank you. You're welcome. Was there anything else that I missed to ask about? No, I don't think so. Okay. That sounds good. So if there was nothing else that you wanted to share, we'll get that started and I'll be back shortly. Okay, sounds good. Thank you.",1.0,1.0,1.0,0,45,1063,0
RES0003,"D: It's nice to meet you. What's your name? 

P: It's nice to meet you as well. My name is Jenn and I'm here with my son Joey here, who he's had a sore throat now for the last couple of days. 

D: OK, how old is he, Joey? 

P: Uh, he is 3 years old. 

D: He's three years old, OK. And you said for the past couple days, so about 2-3 days?

P: Yeah, probably yeah about 3 days ago he he didn't go to school for the last two days because, or I mean daycare I should say because the pains but was bugging him so bad.

D: OK, yeah um. So how long has he been going to daycare for?

P: He started this year, so, um, he's been going for about six months. 

D: OK? Is he having issues swallowing food? Does it hurt when he swallows food?

P: Yeah, he's, uh, he's definitely the last couple of days hasn't been eating as much like solid food. He's drinking cold liquids okay but yeah, he hasn't been eating as much. 

D: OK. 

P: He says it's hard to. He does say it hurts to swallow as well.

D: OK, and does does he ever clutch to his neck like his neck hurts?

P: No, he hasn't said anything like that. I mean nothing about his neck. 

D: OK, um, have you taken his temperature at all?

P: Yeah we did and it's uh, it's pretty high actually, it was like 39.4. 

D: OK wow, yeah that's pretty high. Have you noticed any swollen areas on his neck?

P: No, not I haven't noticed anything on his neck. 

D: OK, any rashes that you've noticed? 

P: No rashes.

D: No, OK. And has he been having chills or night sweats? 

P: Um, nothing like that that we've noticed, no shaking or or sweaty bed.

D: OK, and how about like a stuffy nose or runny nose?

P: Uh, no, nothing like that. 

D: OK, and coughing? 

P: No cough. 

D: No, and how about is he complaining of any body aches?

P: No, it's mostly just been is his throat his throat that he's complaining about.

D: OK, how about headaches?

P: Uh, He hasn't mentioned anything with his head. 

D: OK, and has he been around anyone who's been sick?  Maybe at his daycare? 

P: I, I mean, his sister has had had some colds. She's also in his daycare. So I mean, maybe her.

D: OK, how old is she?

P: Um she's 2.

D: She's two. OK, so she's younger.

P: Yeah.

D: OK, any nausea or vomiting? 

P: Ah no vomiting.

D: OK, how about um, diarrhea, constipation?

P: Haven't noticed anything like that, his his bowel movements have been normal.

D: How about urinating, has that been normal?

P: His usual amount is as, as far as I know.

D: OK. And OK, any issues with his eyes? Any like pus or bleeding or redness? 

P: No, his eyes of have looked normal to me. 

D: OK, how about his ears?

P: Those have also been normal. 

D: OK, any sores on his mouth or inside?

P: Um no, it does kinda look like there. It's pretty red in the back of his throat when I was able to look, but yeah.

D: OK, and has he ever experienced any of these symptoms before?

P: Um, he's had sore throats before, but I think this one is a bit more severe. He hasn't complained this bad before. 

D: OK, OK. Um has he tried anything for it? Have you given him any over the counter medications?

P: Yeah, we we did use some Tylenol and it brought the fever down so that was part of the reason why we we didn't come in 'cause he's had sore throats before but the fever bounced back and and the pain seems to have continued so we came in. 

D: Ok, OK. And is he otherwise healthy? Does he have any medical conditions?

P: Uh, yeah, he's otherwise healthy no medical conditions, um hasn't been, had a reason to see a doctor before. 

D: No, OK. And then just how was pregnancy with him? Was it normal? Any complications?

P: Um yeah there, so had um gestational diabetes, but it was treated, it was treated with diet. Um and blood sugars have been fine now, but no complications to the pregnancy from that regard as far as I know.

D: OK, any alcohol or recreational drugs used during the pregnancy?

P: No, nothing like that. No. No smoking either. 

D: OK, OK, good um and how far along were you when when you delivered him?

P: Um it was a vaginal delivery just after 38 weeks. OK so he was full term.

D: And you said vaginal delivery? Did they have to induce you at all? 

P: Um no no. 

D: OK and was he a normal birth weight? 

P: Yeah he was. Yeah, I think he was like just over 3 kilograms.

D: OK, good and was he healthy after birth? Did he have any breathing issues? Jaundice? Anything like that? 

P: Um, no breathing issues or or jaundice. He came home with us right away.

D: OK, OK and then after that point to now has he been normal in terms of his weight, height, head circumference? 

P: Yeah yeah. He's been growing normally and eating well up up to this point. 

D: OK, and I should ask um has he been hitting all his milestones like, is he doing the things that his peers are doing?

P: Yeah, I would say he's keeping up with his his peers in daycare and no concerns with his development. 

D: OK, good. Is he on any medications? 

P: No medications.

D: No. OK, and is he up to date with all his immunizations?

