d to different areas of your body at all uh it just starts gradually going away at when when i stop coughing okay have you experienced any kind of headaches when nausea or vomiting No Okay So you mentioned you had some chills but you don know if you had a fever Mm-hmm. Okay. Have you experienced any kind of dizziness or fainting spells? No. Okay. and have you been in contact with anyone who has been ill recently um not that i know of no okay have you experienced any night sweats i feel chilly at night but i don't maybe yeah okay any significant weight loss recently no Okay. And have you noticed any kind of symptoms like your heart is racing or anything like that? No. Okay. Have you experienced any changes in your bowel movements at all, like any constipation or diarrhea? No. Any changes in your urinary patterns? No. Okay. Any issues with your sleep or appetite at all? No. Okay. Have you had any recent infections, like a cold or anything like that recently? I guess I had a runny nose a few days before. Okay. Yeah. Have you at all been exposed to anyone with tuberculosis in the past? No. Okay. Any exposure at your workplace or at home to any fumes or dust, any pets or animals? Well, I have birds, but I've had them for a while. Okay. How long have you had the birds for? About three years. Okay. But they haven't caused you any issues before? No. Okay. And do you have any allergies that you know of? No allergies. Okay. Any past medical conditions like high blood pressure, diabetes, asthma? No. Any previous surgeries? No, none. Okay. Any hospitalizations for any reason? No. Okay. Are you on any medications currently? No. And do you have any family history of any medical conditions like cancers or heart attacks or any lung issues? No. Okay. And currently do you work? I do The place I work is very crowded and it not the best conditions to work in And there an air conditioner which I think is broken It quite humid It never been checked Yeah And how long have you been working