␀","What brings you in? Hi. I've just been a little bit worried that for the last couple of months, I noticed I've been getting more and more out of breath when I've been doing exercise. And I know I got a brother who had a heart issue, and I'm just really concerned that I might have something wrong with my ticker. I just want to get it checked out, you know? Yeah, for sure. When did the shortness of breath start? so this winter specifically like we haven't been too active because of covid this year we've just been staying in the house all last year but with the snow i gotta be shoveling snow whenever it fell and before i could be able like two years ago i'd be able to clear the driveway no problem but now even after half the driveway i've noticed i'm getting consistently out of breath i've got this nasty cough and it's prompted my wife to kind of get me to come in she's a little bit worried yeah so it's mostly on exertion it doesn't happen at rest is that correct being out of breath yeah No? Okay. Okay. And has this ever happened to you before? Yeah. About a year and a half ago, we went down to Toronto in order to see the CN Tower and just, you know, do tourist stuff. And we tried climbing a couple of flights of stairs, you know, just to do a little bit. And I could not. I always saw myself pretty healthy, pretty active, but it really took the wind out of my sails. So I had to stop, stooped over, just couldn't do it. And how did you manage, like how was that treated at that time? How did you get better? Oh, I didn't do any. I just attributed to being, I don't know, out of shape a little bit. I worked as a mechanic when I was younger. I was pretty active, but ever since retiring, I thought I'd keep up. At least my stamina wouldn't go away that quickly, but I chalked it up to being out of shape and went home. Okay. So your shortness of breath seems to be getting worse. Yeah. Right? Okay. Any coughing with that? Yeah. Yeah. Not necessarily when I noticed it. when I was shoveling the driveway, but I've had a cough for the last couple of years. Usually in the morning, I just bring up a little bit of gunk, but most of my buddies have that, just like a morning cough, you know? Yeah, and the gunk that you bring up, what color is it? Yellow, sometimes a little brown. Okay, and when did that start? Oof, that's been going on the last 10 years. Well, to be honest, since I've been like 30. but it's been fairly consistent last 10 years i'd say okay any blood that you bring up uh not that i've noticed like bright red no nothing like that okay any wheezyness yeah yeah i noticed that when i was shoveling yeah when i was out of breath it sound sound different sound different than being usually out of breath. It sounded wheezy. Okay. Any chest pain? Yeah, a little bit, actually. At rest? No, nothing like that. Nothing when I'm not moving. Okay. So the chest pain, when did that start? First noticed it this winter on the driveway, but it wasn't like I know what they say about a heart that's supposed to like be crushing pain in your chest that moves up your neck nothing like that like my lungs my throat like you're really really out of breath you know okay so you attributing it mostly to your shortness of breath then I think so I really hope this is my heart I never had a heart attack Yeah Where in your chest is this chest pain happening? Like, is it central? Is it more towards the left, towards the right? It was kind of both sides. Okay. It was, yeah, all across my chest. To be honest, it was only the one time that I was really struggling. and I coughed up a bit. Yeah. Okay. Any pain in your calves or legs after you walk a certain distance? No, no. No. Do you ever feel like your heart's racing? I felt like my heart was racing after that much activity, but no, not usually. Okay. How about swelling in your limbs? No, nothing like that. Okay. Any fainting spells or dizziness? No, never fainted in my life. Okay. Any confusion, memory loss? No, nothing like that. Headaches? Headaches. You know I do get headaches from time to time. I associate them with stress, but I haven't been too stressed out recently, so nothing in the last couple of years. Okay. Any neck stiffness? Nope. No, okay. Any sensitivity to light or loud sounds associated with that headache? No, nothing like that. Okay. Any weight loss? No, I wish. Okay. Fevers? No. Rashes? you know i got these weird things on my head i think mainly because of the sun like these brown patches but that wouldn't be a rash would it i have to examine that closer um if you think it's associated with the sun it could be something like seborrheic keratosis um but i'd have to see what what they look like so we can take a look at that later. That's okay. So any changes in your vision or hearing? Nope. No. Steffy nose, runny nose? I had a bit of a cold a couple months ago, but no, not that recent. Okay. Sore throat? Yeah, a little bit after the cough. I had a little bit of a sore throat, but went away pretty quickly. Change in smell or taste? I haven't been able to smell or taste too well for a while. What's a while? Ten years? Seven years? It's been more salt, more spices on my food, you know. Okay, okay. Any changes to your bowel habits? Nope. Been regular all my life. Nausea, vomiting? Nope. Okay. Joint pain, muscle aches? You know, my knees have been giving me trouble for a while, but nothing recent, no. Okay. And are you otherwise healthy? Nope. I've got high blood pressure, see the doc about that. High cholesterol, see the doc about that. and yeah, I don't know, gone to a car crash in my 40s, broke my arm one time, nothing else really. Okay, any surgeries? I think I had my appendix out when I was, yeah, I had my appendix out when I was like 12. Okay. No, never been under the knife since then. Okay, good. Have you been taking any medications for that high blood pressure? Yeah. Doc's got me on two blood pressure medications and one cholesterol medication. Okay. And do you take those frequently? Yeah, every day. Okay, good. Any other medications? Nope. Okay. Are you up to date with all your immunizations? Gee it been a while since I got an immunization I think yeah I Okay Once you turn 65 they usually give you shingrex to prevent shingles and a pneumovax vaccine to prevent pneumococcal infections Have you had those ones? Nope. No? Okay, so if you're interested in getting those, we can discuss that at some point today as well. Okay. Do you have any allergies? No. No? Okay. Okay, so you mentioned a family history of your brother having congenital heart disease. Any other heart diseases that run in the family? Congenital? What's that mean? Like something that you're born with. No, I don't think he's ever born a thing. He had a couple heart attacks. Oh, heart attacks. Okay, sorry. I must have misinterpreted that. How old was he when you had his first heart attack? He's older than me by five years, but he had the first one when I was younger than I am now, like 62. Was the first one, another one at 65. Okay. Okay. Do they ever find a cause for his heart attack? Is he a healthy person? Healthy. He's healthy. You know, I wouldn't call him too healthy of a guy. He's a hard liver, let's call him that. Why it happened? I think, honestly, it's his diet. Man eats like a hog. Steaks, butter, bacon. I'm assuming that's what did him in. Oh, yikes. Okay. Okay. Any other heart conditions that run in the family or other members of the family experiencing heart attacks? Yep. Dad died young from a heart attack. He died younger than I am now. He passed away at 66. Oh, I'm sorry to hear that. Oh, it's been years now. Yeah. That's what it is. His grandmother had a stroke, high blood pressure on my mom's side, high cholesterol on my mom's side, too. But, yeah, an awful heart attack on my father's side of the family. Okay. Any other lung conditions that were in the family? None that come to mind. Okay. And do you smoke? Yeah. Yeah, I smoke. Okay. How much do you smoke? I cut it back about half a pack a day the last two years now. Okay. And before that? It was pretty much a pack a day. Maybe when I was bad, two packs a day. But I've been smoking, yeah, since about, when did I start working at the shop? Like 17? Everyone there smokes. Okay. Wow, yeah. It's been a while then. But it's good that you cut down. That's good. Do you do any other recreational drugs like marijuana, cocaine, heroin, anything? I'll smoke weed at the shop every Friday, but I'm not a huge fan of it, to be honest. Okay. And how much do you smoke every Friday? go through about four joints seven people so i don't know what that is half a gram half a joint half okay yeah okay and do you drink oh yeah how much do you drink let's see christmas was about the last time i went ahead i had like a beer or two weekends, but when family's in town, we'll go whole hog. I'll drink maybe 20 beer. Oh, okay. Okay. Yeah, you should... Have you thought about cutting that down You got to keep up with the family you know You can let them embarrass you like that I understand that But also, you know, it's important to take care of your health and slow and steady wins the race, right? I'll keep that in mind, dog. Yeah. And how's your diet? Been pretty good. The wife's been on a health food craze last five years. Vegetables, I don't know. I eat whatever she cooks, basically. Okay. That's good. And in terms of exercise, do you get to move around? I used to be pretty active. I used to bike around. But because of COVID, I've just been indoors all this time. So, no, not much. Okay. Okay, well, it's good to go for a walk once in a while. I think that's allowed during COVID as long as you're being safe. And who do you live with at home? I live with my wife. Okay. Any children? Yeah, I've got three kids. One for my first marriage, two with the missus right now. Okay. Do you get to see them often? Yeah, his daughter lives in town. I'm going to see her in the grand cabin a bit. Other boy works at Fort Mac, and my oldest son, he's out east. Okay. Don't get to see him too much. okay and have you had any contacts with people who've been sick recently no we've been keeping entirely to ourselves you can get our groceries ordered to the house okay and how about travel any recent travel nope no okay um And then lastly, I just wanted to ask you, because you have been smoking for a long time, have you ever been diagnosed with something called COPD? Doesn't ring a bell. No? Okay. Have you ever had any pulmonary function tests or chest x-rays done in the past? Chest x-ray. I think they did a chest x-ray after the car crash. Okay. But I can't think of getting one recently, no. Okay. All right. Well, those are all the questions that I had for you. Did you have any questions for me? So this is a heart. Like, should I be worried? Yeah. You know what? It sounds from what you're telling me, it sounds like you have shortness of breath, on exertion. It sounds like you have a cough with producing some phlegm. It doesn't seem like you have any systemic symptoms of infection. So I'm not too worried about that. And then in terms of your heart, you mentioned you had that chest pain once, but it really does sound more like a lung problem to me than a heart problem to me right now. But of course, we'll do all the necessary investigations to rule out any heart stuff. But right now I'm thinking it could be something called COPD, chronic obstructive pulmonary disorder. because of your smoking history. So we'll start with doing a pulmonary function test and chest x-ray. And we'll try to go from there. If it is COPD, we'll likely put you on a puffer for that, like a long-acting beta agonist. That's what it's called. So if your symptoms don't get better with that, we'll do other investigations to try to figure out what this is. How does that sound? Sounds great, Doc. Thanks a million. All right. Great. Thank you. Have a good one.",1.0,1.0,1.0,0,42,2284,0
RES0055,"D: What brings you in?

P: Hi, yes I just came in today because I've been a bit concerned about some breathing difficulties over the last few days. It all started out with like a cough over the last week, but now I'm having trouble breathing as well.

D: Oh OK, well I'm sorry to hear that. So you said a cough as well, so the cough at least a week back and the shortness of breath or difficulty breathing, when did that start? 

P: So yeah, the cough, I usually have a cough. I've had COPD for a long time, but this past week the coughing has been much worse with a lot of more sputum and. Other than that, it started I would say two to three days ago. The cough got worse and then every time I'm moving around I like have to sit down and catch my breath, which is pretty abnormal for me.

D: OK yeah, so alright. So let's focus on the cough first. You said it's a wet cough?

P: Yes, I am producing a lot of sputum. 

D: OK, what color is your sputum?

P: It's mainly like clear white.

D: OK yeah so you don't see yellow pus or anything green or bloody in there?

P: No, I don't think so. But there's definitely like a lot more than what I usually produce.

D: OK, umm this cough, does it sound harsh, barky or does it sound muffled?

P: I would say it's a bit harsh at times. I wouldn't say it's barky or muffled. I do find myself wheezing a little over the last few days as well. 

D: OK. Do you find you have any chest pain associated with the shortness of breath?

P: Oh no, I don't really have any pains.

D: OK, and have you ever experienced anything like this before?

P: I did a couple of years ago, I had to be admitted because I had some shortness of breath. 

D: OK.

P: But that was, I think, two years ago. 

D: OK. And when you were admitted two years ago, did they tell you what you had?

P: Yeah, they said I had some kind of lung infection at that time, so they gave me some antibiotics while I was in the hospital.

D: OK, did they ever say to you that you had anything else like asthma, COPD, any longstanding conditions?

P: Yeah so I've had COPD for more than... I guess more than 10 years now so I think it just got a lot worse with the infection.

