e fever any cold symptoms No. Okay. And any exposure to anyone that you know of that might have tuberculosis? No, I've been mostly at home. I haven't really been seeing many people lately. Okay. And do you have any past medical history or any diagnosis like COPD, asthma, high blood pressure, diabetes, anything like that? I had a cataract surgery, but that's about it. Okay. And are there any medications that you take on a daily basis? No. Well, multivitamin. Yeah. Multivitamins. OK. Any allergies that, you know, to medications or any environmental allergies? I think sulfa. But that's it. OK. And what kind of reaction do you get? Oh, I got a rash. Rash. OK. Any surgeries or hospitalizations in the past? I just had a cataract removed in my right eye, and that's about it. Okay. Any contacts of yours that have been sick recently? No. No? Okay. And in terms of your family history, are there any cancers, like lung cancer in your family, or any heart conditions, anything like that? I think my great uncle had lung cancer. My mom had type 2 diabetes, but that's it. Okay. And currently right now, do you work? Yeah, I'm retiring soon. I work as a bus driver. okay and in the past have you worked in any environments where you were exposed to any metals toxins any asbestos or anything like that um i don't think so okay i worked as a bus driver for for quite a number of years now okay and uh where do you live right now in an apartment and a home and who do you live with? I live in a home with my wife and it's just us two. And do you know if there's any like asbestos exposure in your in your home at all? I don't think so. No. Okay. And currently do you smoke? um i been cutting down but um i do smoke yes i i was um smoke about a half a pack per day now um there was a time i was smoking two packs per day uh for a number of years um and i started smoking when i was probably 15 yeah so it's been about 40 yeah 40-ish years at least and have you uh thought of quitting at all yeah i've been trying um it would be um nice to uh i was thinking of maybe get talking about a prescription for helping quit or or something like that today because i was feeling like this is causing some like my cough and um shortness of breath yeah well it's really great that you're thinking about quitting we can definitely help you with some resources and some medications have you tried anything before that uh i should know to help you quit i've tried nicotine patches um and gum but um that's it okay so yeah there's um like other options as well there's that you can take and now uh have you heard of champix um i did i did hear of it actually yeah So one of my friends tried it and it worked well for them. So, yeah. Okay. Yeah, so we can, if you're wondering about that, I can give you some information on that medication, like a whole package for you, and then we can discuss if that could work for you. That sounds great. Okay, sweet. And other than smoking, do you use any recreational drugs like marijuana? No, I don't. okay uh and do you drink alcohol uh i'll have one or two beers on the weekend okay all right so yeah that's that's pretty much uh all the questions i had um right now it seems that your symptoms uh you do have that cough and the shortness of breath and it's been chronic but now you're coughing up some blood as well so that is definitely something that's concerning and i we want to make sure there's nothing going on so we will get a chest x-ray for you and see um if we can find anything there and um if if are you still producing like the bloody sputum yeah that's been coming up um daily still okay so if if um if you think you can produce that we can even take a sample of that as well and see if there's any presence. The one thing that we're concerned about with some of your symptoms and a long history of smoking as well is lung cancer. So yeah, we will do a chest x-ray, get some cytology done as well. And then once we have that in the future, we may need to maybe d