ions? I have high blood pressure, and I take amylotipine for that. Okay. Any other over-the-counter medications or any other medications are you wrong? No. Any allergies? No allergies. Okay. And where do you currently live? In a townhouse just outside of the city here. I see. I see. Do you live alone? No, I live with my wife and daughter. And have you or your wife or your daughter been sick recently or have either of you had contact with someone who been sick I've been working from home, but my daughter has recently started going back to high school. and she's had a runny nose recently and a sore throat, but that's about it. And what about your wife? She's been fine. Yeah, she's been healthy. Okay, good. Other than your daughter, have you been in contact with anyone else who might be sick or might have symptoms similar to what your daughter has? I don't think so. Okay. All right. And have you traveled anywhere recently? No. I've been just working from home. Okay. And do you smoke? No. Ever smoked in the past? No, I've never smoked before. Marijuana? I mean, I'll have a joint sometimes with friends at a party or something, but that's, I mean, maybe once a month. Sure. And any street drugs? Nope, nothing like that. Okay, and do you drink alcohol? I'll have a beer a couple of times per week. All right, all right. And you told me about your medical history, but have you ever had any surgeries or any hospitalizations in the past? I've had a hernia repair about seven years ago. I haven't had any issues since. All right, okay. And are there any medical conditions that run in your family? Um, my grandfather had a heart attack in his 70s. And I think my dad has high blood pressure as well. But I think that's it. All right. Well, so I think that's all that I wanted to know. I can see that you haven't been feeling well over the past couple of days. and I'll go talk to my attending and we'll come back and chat with you a little bit more and do a physical exam and go from there.