 be a dry cough sometimes I had some um it was more of a wet cough but it was it was usually just this white uh thing coming up it wasn't like there was never blood before okay uh and you're coughing more often as well over this last month. Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah. Okay. Have you been experiencing any headaches? No. Okay. How about any eye pain or ear pain? No, no, no. How about any eye redness or discharge? Nope. Any runny nose or sore throat? Nope. Okay. Have you had any fevers or chills? I checked my fevers. I checked my temperature a couple of days ago. It was just a little bit. I think it was 38. Okay. So, yeah, that would be a fever. It was, I think, two weeks ago. Okay. Do you feel hot now? Not really. No. Okay. Have you had any night sweats? No. And have you had any weight loss over the last several months? Oh, yeah. How much weight? About 20 pounds. Okay. So how long was that weight loss over? I'd say about three months, three, four months. okay and and sorry what um was your starting weight um yeah yeah i was uh um 210 pounds okay um and so yeah about a 10 percent reduction in your weight over the last couple of months it sounds like um okay how was your appetite been? It okay All right And have you been having any chest pain No Any wheeze? No. Have you had any dizziness or lightheadedness? No, no. Okay. How about any nausea or vomiting? No. Any diarrhea or constipation? No. Any urinary problems? No. Any skin rashes or muscle aches? No. Okay. And have you been diagnosed with any medical conditions before? Yeah, I've been diagnosed with COPD, with high blood pressure and high cholesterol. I see. All right. And do you take any medications for those? I take Lipidor. And I take some buffers, but I don't use them very frequently. I forget to use them. And I tried them, but they haven't been very helpful these past two months. Okay. So you've tried them when you were short of breath and they haven't helped? They haven't done much. Okay. And are you allergic to any medications or have any allergies? No. All right. And have you been hospitalized for any reason or like including COPD exacerbation or any similar symptoms? I was actually hospitalized about four or five times last year. and uh was this for copd exacerbations yeah yeah okay did those each require a stay in the hospital i mean two or three of them i did yeah okay um and uh have you had any surgeries i know um and uh are you currently uh smoking yeah okay how much do you smoke uh per day um i've cut it down quite a bit um i only have two cigarettes a day i used to have a back and a half uh but i've cut it down a lot i'm trying to i'm trying to quit but it's hard yeah for sure it's great that you're working towards quitting we can discuss that further and there are several options that might be available to help if it something you interested in Because yeah it definitely really hard Do you drink alcohol Once in a while on Christmas. Okay. And do you use any recreational drugs? No. Do you smoke marijuana or use marijuana products? No. All right. And who are you living with currently? I live with my wife. Okay. And are you looking after the home and like functionally independent right now? Yeah. I use a cane. Okay. And, you know, my son comes over and helps out with groceries and my wife cooks. But I help out with cleaning sometimes. Okay, great. And so are you retired? Yeah. Okay. And has anybody in the family had any heart or lung conditions? My dad died of lung cancer. He was a big smoker as well. And my mom had a heart attack. Okay. And how old were your parents approximately? Yeah, my dad was 65, and my mom was very young. She was 50. I see. Did your mom survive the heart attack? No, no, she did not. I'm sorry to hear that. And lung cancer, you mentioned. Any other cancers that run in the family? No. Okay. So that was all the questions I wanted to ask on history. certainly it sounds like you're bringing up some blood with the increased cough and with difficulties breathing so we will get a chest x-ray and possibly a CT image of your chest as well to see if there's anything going on in your lungs and we might do some blood work as well to check a few things. So we'll get those ordered and see what that shows. Thank you.",0.22469490308686288,0.22026741731175228,0.2840703459271523,28,190,95,1108
RES0097,"D: How can I help you today?

