 Do you have any shortness of breath or chest pain at all? No. Any sore throat or muscle aches? No. Any headaches? Nope. Have you traveled at all recently? No. Have you had any nausea or vomiting? No. Any fevers or chills? No. Any night sweats or fatigue? No. Any kind of sensation that your heart is racing? No, nothing like that. Any changes in your bowel movements like constipation or diarrhea? No. Any changes in your urinary pattern? No Any issues with your sleep or appetite No Have you lost any weight significant weight recently in the last few months no and um are you do you have any exposure to like fumes dust or like uh pets or animals anything that you might have an allergic reaction to No, nothing like that. Okay. And currently are you sexually active? I am. And can you just tell me a little bit of a detail about your partner and if you've had any new partners recently at all? No, I've been with the same partner for the past five years. Okay. And do you have any history of any STIs? No. Okay. All right. In terms of your past medical history, do you have any diagnoses or any medical conditions at all? No, nothing longstanding. Anything you take medications for? No. Are you allergic to any medications? Not medications. Any environmental allergies? Just, yeah, some seasonal allergies. Okay. Any previous hospitalizations or surgeries? I was hospitalized for like an appendectomy when I was younger, but that's about it. And when was that? That was when I was 18. Okay. And any complications after that? No. And in terms of your family history does anyone have any lung conditions heart conditions or any cancers Nope nothing like that And currently do you work I do. I work from home, though. And how would you describe your living situation right now? I live in an apartment with my partner, and we have a dog. And currently, do you smoke at all? No. Do you use any recreational drugs like marijuana? No. How about any alcohol? I drink like a glass of wine every other day. Okay. Yeah, so those are some of the questions I had for you. I know it's a bit concerning because of the pandemic going on, and a runny nose can be a symptom of COVID as well, but it can also be a symptom of just the common cold or any other virus. but since you're having your symptomatic right now we will definitely get like a COVID swab test done for you and if you start having any just monitor for your symptoms you should have the test back within 48 hours until then at least for 14 days you should try to isolate in your own room wear a mask around your partner and not go outside. So just self-isolate. Okay. And then you will get the test results back hopefully in a few days. So do you have any questions at all? No, thank you. That was good. Okay. Take care. Bye. You too.",0.1839402427637722,0.1837686567164179,0.21529167832519036,1,161,35,875
