ometimes and a fever that's started a bit more recently, as well as having some night sweats. Yeah. Have you experienced any other symptoms? No. Other than that, no symptoms. I see. And have you tried anything to make the symptoms better? I've tried some Tylenol. I tried some like cough suppressants but nothing seems to be helping Okay Okay And have you been diagnosed with any medical conditions before No, not. Well, actually, I have osteoporosis, for which I'm taking calcium and vitamin D, as well as, like, alendronate, alendronate, some sort of bisphosphonate. Okay. Have you had any bone fractures? I had a hip fracture like two years ago. Okay. And how has the recovery and mobility been? Pretty good now. Oh, that's great. And do you have any other medical conditions besides osteoporosis? this? No, not that I know. And have you had any surgeries aside from the hip surgery two years ago? I had my wisdom teeth taken out. I've had my gallbladder taken out. And I I had a PE a long time ago. Okay. And what happened around that time with the pulmonary embolism? Was there a trigger, like a surgery around that time, or were you immobilized or anything? Yeah, they think it happened right after my gallbladder removal because I was in the hospital for a while. Okay. And so were you on any medication for a period of time after that? Yeah, I was, but not anymore. Okay. Okay. And are you taking any other medications besides the ones for your bones? No, no other medications. And do you have any allergies? No. Okay. And then could you tell me a little bit about your living situation right now? Are you living with anybody and whereabouts? I live in an apartment by myself and it's in London. Okay, great. And do you have any supports in the home that help you with any activities of daily living, like either dressing or bathing or making food or even doing some of the shopping? So I am pretty independent for most things. There will be like a CCAC care worker who comes in once in a whi