 of any cancers, any lung cancer or anything like that? No. And currently do you work or are you retired? I'm retired. Okay. And what your living situation like right now Do you live with anyone I live with my wife Okay And do you smoke No. Have you ever smoked? I did when I was young. Okay. And how long would you say you smoked for? I'd say 45 years. And how much would you smoke in an average day? About a pack a day. Any reclamational drugs like marijuana? No. And do you drink alcohol? Yeah, I do. I drink a glass every night. And a glass of, what would you drink? Oh, just a glass of wine. White wine. Okay. Okay, so those are all the questions I have. for you today. Any questions for me? No. Okay. So yeah, there's definitely like the coughing and the shortness of breath are definitely concerning and they've been going on for a pretty long time. Do you have any night sweats or anything like that? No. Okay. So there's a few things that we think about with the chronic shortness of breath and the cough. One could be just a COPD diagnosis with your long history of smoking. And this function test will get an x-ray, chest x-ray as well. The other thing that we need to look out for is lung cancer. And since you have been smoking for a pretty long time, even though you may have quit, which is really great, But that long history of smoking, especially also with you working in a mine, those are some things that need to think of as well. And so we may require like a chest x-ray and even a CT scan of your lungs as well. So, yeah, first, we'll just do a couple of tests, do a physical examination, get your vitals, do some blood work and do some of those tests. And then we'll also get a COVID swab test done for you as well, just in case. Does that sound good? Yeah. Great. So we'll be with you shortly.",0.1937984496124031,0.1926040061633282,0.22600140944326985,8,198,44,1048
